        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 2:49PM CDT by NWS Dodge City KS</headline>
        <description>At 248 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Cimarron, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Howell around 255 PM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
